<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="splitting-element" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Splitting Element</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>You can split an element one of these ways:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Split an element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Place the cursor in the element in the <xref href="editing-window.xml">Editing Window</xref>.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Split the element.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>Do one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Choose <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol>
                      </menucascade>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Click the <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol> button <image href="split-element-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> on the toolbar.</p>
                  </li>
                </ul></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
<?serna-redline-start 0 split multiple elements, not just parent one?>      <step>
        <cmd>Split the parent of an element in the Editing Window.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Place the cursor in the element in the <xref href="editing-window.xml">Editing Window</xref>.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Split the parent of the element.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>To split the parent of the element, press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> twice. Or press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> multiple times in a row to split  the parent of the parent of the element and so on.</p>
              <p>This is called <i>advanced</i> element split.</p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
<?serna-redline-end?>      <step>
        <cmd>Split an element in the ContentMap.</cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Click the element in the <xref href="content-map.xml">ContentMap</xref>.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Split the element.</cmd>
            <info>
              <p>Do one of the following:<ul>
                  <li>
                    <p>Choose <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Element</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol>
                      </menucascade>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <p>Click the <uicontrol>Split Element</uicontrol> button <image href="split-element-button.png" align="center" placement="inline"/> on the toolbar.</p>
                  </li>
<?serna-redline-start 1000 ?>                  <li>
                    <p>Use context menu.</p>
                  </li>
<?serna-redline-end?>                </ul></p>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>The <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> key won&apos;t work to split elements in the ContentMap and consequently the <i>advanced split</i> won&apos;t work.</p>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <example>
      <title>Example. Splitting elements.</title>
      <p>Suppose we have inserted <codeph>itemizedlist</codeph>-&gt;<codeph>listitem</codeph>-&gt;<codeph>para</codeph>.</p>
<?serna-redline-start 0 lets simplify this example
- type "OrangeLemon"
- split into "Orange" "Lemon"
- split into separate items?>      <fig frame="all">
        <image href="inserted-listitem.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      </fig>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>Type &quot;<codeph>Orange</codeph>&quot; in the <codeph>para</codeph>. Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol>.</p>
          <p>The <codeph>para</codeph> will be split (a new <codeph>para</codeph> will be inserted).</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="split-para.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Do not type anything in the new <codeph>para</codeph>. Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> immediately again.</p>
          <p>This will split the first  <codeph>listitem</codeph>.</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="split-advanced.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Type &quot;<codeph>Lemon</codeph>&quot; in the <codeph>para</codeph>. Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> twice to split the <codeph>listitem</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Type &quot;<codeph>Apple</codeph>&quot; in the <codeph>para</codeph>. Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> twice to split the <codeph>listitem</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Type &quot;<codeph>Lime</codeph>&quot; in the <codeph>para</codeph>. Press <uicontrol>Enter</uicontrol> once to split the <codeph>para</codeph>.</p>
          <fig frame="all">
            <image href="list-to-join.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
      </ol>
<?serna-redline-end?>    </example>
  </taskbody>
</task>
